cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on developing a novel network architecture to cope with the mobile data tsunami caused by user-generated content. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes caching policies and analyzes the outage probability and average delivery rate, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system design with randomly located base stations and massive MIMO, which can be analyzed using systems and control theory. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper investigates the impact of the target bitrate on the network performance, which is related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes the modified von Mises distribution as the popularity distribution function for caching policies, which can be analyzed using data structures and algorithms.
